South Africa  posted a budget
deficit of 136.6 billion rand in the year through March,
compared with 167.6 billion rand in the previous year, the
National Treasury said.  The deficit was 4.9 billion rand in the month, down from
11.7 billion rand in March 2010, the Treasury said on its
website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
